# SclJet SQL INSERT / DELETE

`executeMutation` runs `INSERT INTO t VALUES (…)` and `DELETE FROM t WHERE …` against a
database image, threading the new image through the balanced write path. After a sequence
of inserts and deletes the table is byte-for-value identical to reference sqlite3 running
the same statements (verified out-of-band, integrity_check ok); here the query results are
locked across backends.

[ByteSlice, SqliteValue, SqlInteger, SqlText, buildTableDatabase](std/scljet/index.ssc)
[queryImage, renderRows, executeMutation](std/scljet/sql.ssc)

```scalascript
def apply(db: ByteSlice, sql: String): ByteSlice =
  executeMutation(db, sql) match
    case Left(m) =>
      println(sql + " => ERR:" + m)
      db
    case Right(next) => next

def show(db: ByteSlice, sql: String): Unit =
  queryImage(db, sql) match
    case Left(m) => println(sql + " => ERR:" + m)
    case Right(rows) => println(sql + " => " + renderRows(rows).toString)

buildTableDatabase(512, 1, 1, "t", "CREATE TABLE t(id INTEGER, name TEXT)",
  List(List(SqlInteger(1L), SqlText("a")),
       List(SqlInteger(2L), SqlText("b")))) match
  case Left(error) => println("build-error:" + error.message)
  case Right(db0) =>
    val db1 = apply(db0, "INSERT INTO t VALUES (3, 'c')")
    val db2 = apply(db1, "INSERT INTO t VALUES (4, 'd')")
    val db3 = apply(db2, "INSERT INTO t VALUES (5, 'e')")
    show(db3, "SELECT * FROM t")
    val db4 = apply(db3, "DELETE FROM t WHERE id = 2")
    val db5 = apply(db4, "DELETE FROM t WHERE name = 'd'")
    show(db5, "SELECT * FROM t")
    show(db5, "SELECT name FROM t WHERE id >= 3")
    val db6 = apply(db5, "INSERT INTO t VALUES (6, 'f')")
    show(db6, "SELECT id, name FROM t")
```
